Note: Phew, at long last, this Eula doujin has been translated. Melonbooks lists the doujin to be 30 pages, but the raws I got, only had 27. So it seems those pages have been lost, and as this doujin is somewhat of a lost relic, might never be recovered. Well there are some websites listing it, but they're at an exorbitantly high price, and I will not bother with them. I would be glad if there were someone who could get me those lost pages though. I would love to preserve this masterpiece.
In other news, the next doujin I will be working on, is most likely the Scarlet doujinshi by Gomahangetsu. Until then, happy new year, and see you guys soon! Peace!
